  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Business Strategy Associate/Expert",
  "description": "<p><strong>About the Role</strong></p><p>We are looking for a highly analytical and business-minded <strong>Business Strategy Associate/Expert </strong>to join our APAC Strategy & Operations team.</p><p>This role will be responsible for driving core analytical work in strategy development, business performance analysis, and market research across the APAC region.<br /></p><p><strong>Main Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Participate in the development of APAC’s mid- to long-term strategy, including industry trend studies and competitive landscape analysis.</li><li>Design and drive key strategic initiatives from concept to execution.</li><li>Build and refine the business performance analysis framework for the APAC region.</li><li>Track and analyze key business metrics, identify issues and improvement opportunities.</li><li>Deliver actionable insights to guide business and strategic decision-making.</li><li>Prepare high-quality strategic reports, business analysis papers, and recommendations for senior management.</li><li>Participate in leadership meetings and discussions, providing data-backed insights.</li></ul><p><strong> Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>3–5 years working experience in strategy / business analytics / operations strategy teams with consultancy backgroud, or internet or financial industry</li><li>Experience in business performance analysis, proven ability to independently complete business or operational analysis tasks (e.g., identifying causes of metric fluctuations and proposing improvement actions).</li><li>Experience conducting market research and translating findings into actionable business insights.</li><li>Experience contributing to strategic planning</li><li>Strong ability to define, structure, and solve complex business problems.</li><li>Able to use chinese as working lanaguage to align with chinese speaking stakeholders</li></ul>",
